May 20, 2017 at the International Alatoo University held an investment show "Akkula-Tank". Its organizers were the SAB Incubation Center at the International University "Ala-Too", CreaLab at the Kyrgyz Economic University and the ISC "Entrepreneurship Development Fund" OJSC. The event was supported by the project "I invest in Kyrgyzstan" and the telecommunications operator "Sky Mobile".
The main concept of the investment show is the creation of a unique platform for the presentation, discussion and promotion of business ideas for start-up entrepreneurs, as well as initiating a dialogue between start-ups and potential investors.

14 innovative projects were presented, which were evaluated by the members of the Bid Evaluation Committee on the following criteria:

• The impact of the idea / project on society;
• The urgency and novelty of the idea;
• Hypotheses tested in the market;
• Monetization

Team: a combination of talents, a variety of skills and experience
3 projects were awarded by jury-investors and received investments for further development.

1. The "TMS" project, whose goal is to create a media portal and maintain the rating of the media stream in Kyrgyzstan, received an investment of 300 thousand soms;
2. The founders of the "BooDoo" project, who produce the most delicious baked donuts in the city and want to expand, received funding of 100 thousand soms;
3. And the guys with the project "Smart Study" are inspired by the idea of ​​preparing our graduates for ORT testing through the site and the mobile application and make every effort to implement it. They will receive their investment with the beginning of the new school year.

The event was accompanied by a dynamic show program with elements such as a presentation of the 3D Printer Project from Sanarip Electronics, a laser show, as well as the performance of KVN Kelechek and Kyrgyz stars.

